article.headline: Alabama A&amp,M 69, Tennessee St. 67
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Ala. -- Casey Cantey stole the ball with four seconds left in a tie ball game and hit a pair of free throws a second later, giving Alabama A&M a 69-67 win over Tennessee State on Sunday night. The Bulldogs (2-4) scored five unsanswered points in the last 10 seconds in the win. Down 66-62 with 17 seconds to go, Trant Simpson stole the ball and turned it into a layup cutting the Bulldogs' deficit to two points. After a free throw by Darius Cox put the Tigers (3-5) back ahead by three, Simpson hit a 3-pointer to tie the game with 6 seconds to go. Tennessee State's Gerald Robinson then turned the ball over to Cantey. Alabama A&M erased a six-point halftime deficit and outscored the Tigers 45-37 in the second half. Cornelius Hester led Alabama A&M with 21 points. Jerrell Houston scored a game-high 25 points to lead the Tigers.
